##  ** Accentis - the company **

Accentis Pty Ltd is a leading Australian developer of accounting and business
management (ERP) software.

Based on Brisbane's North side, we are a very stable and established company.
We have been developing and supporting software for over 20 years with
customers in Australia, New Zealand, US and UK.

We complement our highly functional software with an exceptional standard of
service, support and product knowledge

We are a company who believes in excellence in everything that we do.

##  ** Our flagship product - Accentis Enterprise **

Accentis Enterprise is a fully-integrated business management system that
includes accounting and financials, customers and CRM, purchasing and
inventory control, manufacturing, payroll/HR and other key business functions.

Our software is highly configurable and allows us to build solutions for
customers within the software itself to enhance its standard functionality.

We invest a substantial amount into research and development to ensure that
Accentis Enterprise continues to be a market leader.

##  ** Our customers **

Our customers operate in a variety of industries such as pharmaceutical and
medical, food and beverage, Formula-1 and performance automotive, electronics,
aviation and aeronautical, metal and plastics, horticulture, agriculture and
more. They engage in a wide range of activities including wholesaling,
manufacturing and fabrication, warehousing, online shops, servicing, retail
and and professional services.

Our customers range from family businesses up to multi-million dollar
corporate, global groups and ASX-listed companies.

##  ** About the position **

This is a stable and permanent role.

We are looking for someone who wants to be a ** product expert ** and know all
there is to know about how to operate, configure and get best experience from
our software, Accentis Enterprise.

This position will allow you to become fully immersed in a commercial software
application and know how it works, inside and out.

Your role will be a key position in our expanding business and will involve:

  * Implementation of solutions using Accentis Enterprise, including SQL Reports, User interface layout and scripting language 
  * A deep understanding of how our software operates and its capabilities 
  * Working with numbers and data 
  * Data import, export and manipulation with Excel and other tools 
  * Technical support and training for users at all levels 
  * Investigation and problem-solving of simple and complex issues 
  * Technical documentation 
  * Liaising and maintaining good customer relationships 

Every day can bring something new and varied and we are always on-boarding new
customers with unique requirements.

If you are looking for a job that challenges your thinking, encourages you to
look for innovative solutions, and provides something to get your teeth into
then this is the position for you.

##

##  ** About you **

We are looking for someone who thrives on being valued and appreciated, and
who enjoys making a tangible impact on the experience of others.

The following personality attributes are essential and represent the ethos at
Accentis.

  * A polite, courteous, honest and professional demeanour 
  * A strong work ethic and positive attitude towards 
  * An attention to detail. "Near enough" is not good enough at Accentis 
  * A can-do attitude and a desire to get the best result out of every situation 
  * Pride in your work 

You must also possess:

  * Excellent verbal and written communication skills 
  * A logical and organised manner, and an ability to multi-task 
  * A willingness to learn and accept new ideas and concepts 
  * An ability to work efficiently and productively 

You will be trained in all aspects of our software. Having a thirst for
knowledge is essential.

##  ** Your skills **

Any of the following skills will help you secure this position.

  * Experience with SQL, user interface form layout, report design 
  * Experience in managing technical and non-technical customer enquiries 
  * Familiarity with software installation, setup and use 
  * An understanding of how businesses operate internally 
  * Familiarity with business management / ERP software 
  * An understanding of accounting, bookkeeping or business principles 
  * An understanding of inventory management and stock control principles 
  * Technical writing and documentation abilities 

